<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="400" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" type="discussion">
<paragraph lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="400" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,934,1875,1898]" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Remark:</emphasis>
The examination of specimens of all taxa of 
<emphasis box="[865,984,1905,1929]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Styphlidius</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1003,1096,1905,1929]" captionStart="Figs 1 - 9" captionStartId="2.[151,193,1891,1912]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,262,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1434,257,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1 - 9. Habitus of Styphlidius spp. (1) S. italicus Osella, 1981 (Aspromonte, male). (2) Ditto (female). (3) S. brevisetis Osella, 1981 (Kephalonia, male). (4) Ditto (female). (5) S. pelops sp. nov. (Mesohori, male). (6) Ditto (W Agias Sofia, female). (7) S. corcyreus (Reitter, 1884) (Kilkis, male). (8) Ditto (Igoumenitsa, female). (9) Ditto (Reza e kalalit, female)." pageId="0" pageNumber="399">Figs 1-9</figureCitation>
) except 
<taxonomicName box="[1199,1325,1905,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Styphlidius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="399" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosus">
<emphasis box="[1199,1325,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="399">S. globosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[depicted in turn in Osella (1981)] allowed raising 
<taxonomicName box="[607,708,258,281]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Styphlidius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevisetis">
<emphasis box="[607,708,258,281]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">brevisetis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,247,290,314]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Styphlidius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosus">
<emphasis box="[151,247,290,314]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="400">globosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to species level based on the morphological differences given in the key below. Furthermore a new fifth species of the genus is described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
